  "body": "/kind bug\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\nKubelet failed to unmount volumes if the backend ISCSI volume is not available. This also applies to other network attached volumes.\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\nKubelet should be able to unmount the volumes. A manual unmount works even when the backend network volume is not available.\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\nMount an ISCSI/network volume and disconnect/de-provision ISCSI target.\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\nXFS shuts down the filesystem due to I/O errors. Kubelet uses \"stat\" calls to figure out if it is a valid mount point or it is already unmounted. Stat calls fail with EIO and Kubelet never proceeds to unmount the volume.\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`):\r\nKubernetes 1.10.5\r\n- Cloud provider or hardware configuration:\r\nBare metal\r\n- OS (e.g. from /etc/os-release):\r\nCentos 7.4\r\n- Kernel (e.g. `uname -a`):\r\nLinux appserv37 3.10.0-693.el7.x86_64 #1 SMP Tue Aug 22 21:09:27 UTC 2017 x86_64 x86_64 x86_64 GNU/Linux\r\n- Install tools:\r\nManual bring up\r\n- Others:\r\n",
